  "summary": "User behavior is dominated by decision lookup and browsing (ALJ, Board, and Council decisions), which represent the core purpose of the site. Filing and understanding appeals are high-impact but less frequent tasks with potential usability risks due to complexity. The biggest risk is over-prioritizing organizational or informational content while users primarily want fast access to decisions. Validation should focus on confirming the dominance of decision retrieval vs. appeal-related tasks and ensuring navigation supports rapid known-item lookup."
